quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,93,We settled the Israelites in a secure land and provided them with wholesome things. Nor did they disagree among themselves until knowledge was given them. Your Lord will on the Day of Resurrection judge their differences
  10,94,"If you doubt what We have revealed to you, ask those who have read the Book before you. Truth has come to you from your Lord: therefore do not doubt it"
  10,95,"Nor shall you deny God‘s revelations, for then you will be one of the lost"
  10,96,Those for whom the word of your Lord shall be fulfilled will not believe
  10,97,"even if every sign has come to them, until they face the woeful torment"
  10,98,"Were it otherwise, every community, had it believed, would have profited from its faith. But it was so only with Jonah‘s people. When they believed, We spared them the punishment of disgrace in this nether life and suffered them to take their ease a while"
  10,99,"Had your Lord pleased, all the people of the earth would have believed, one and all. Would you then force people to have faith"
  10,100,None can have faith except by God‘s leave. He will visit abomination upon the senseless
  10,101,"Say: ‘Behold what the heavens and the earth contain!‘ But neither signs nor warnings will avail the unbelievers"
  10,102,"What can they wait for but the fate of those who have gone before them? Say: ‘Wait if you will; I will wait with you.‘"
  10,103,We shall save Our apostles and those who believe; it is but just that We should save the faithful